  "text": "In this study, all of the enrolled patients underwent conservative therapy; however, compared with all CLI patients over the same period of time, the proportion of patients receiving conservative therapy was still low. Previous studies have shown that revascularization procedures (e.g., surgery and angioplasty/stenting) can produce a better prognosis than conservative therapy (27) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In terms of patients who are suitable candidates for revascularization, surgery, intervention or a hybrid procedure is still the optimal choice.",
